> The pagination can be influence by providing the request parameters `page` and `pageSize`.

request.description: Returns the amount of items of the given type as a HTTP header field `Item-Count`. On success `HTTP Status 200` is returned. If the type doesnot exist, `HTTP Status 400` is returned.
Checks if the item of the given type exists (`HTTP Status 200`). Otherwise `HTTP Status 404` is returned.

Creates a new item of the given type. The body is a JSON representation of the item.
> The PK must not be set!

On success a `HTTP Status 201` is returned.

Creates or updates an item of the given type, based on the body content (JSON) that represents the properties. If the `PK` property is set, the existing item with this PK is updated. Otherwise a new item is created. On success either a `HTTP Status 201` (new item) or `HTTP Status 202` (update) is returned. If the PK has been provided, but the item is not found, a `HTTP Status 404` is returned.
Updates the item of the given type and PK. If the item doesnot exist, a `HTTP Status 404` is returned. Otherwise `HTTP Status 202` is returned on success.
Deletes the item of the given type and PK. If the items is successfully deleted, `HTTP Status 202` is returned, otherwise `HTTP Status 404`.
